{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Bounds.html#CuspFormClass.qExpansion_isBigO\"><span class=\"name\">CuspFormClass</span>.<span class=\"name\">qExpansion_isBigO</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Γ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Defs.html#Subgroup\">Subgroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/GeneralLinearGroup/Defs.html#Matrix.GeneralLinearGroup\">GL</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Γ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/ArithmeticSubgroups.html#Subgroup.IsArithmetic\">IsArithmetic</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/FunLike/Basic.html#FunLike\">FunLike</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/UpperHalfPlane/Basic.html#UpperHalfPlane\">UpperHalfPlane</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Basic.html#CuspFormClass\">CuspFormClass</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">Γ</span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">F</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.coeff\">PowerSeries.coeff</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/QExpansion.html#ModularFormClass.qExpansion\">ModularFormClass.qExpansion</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Γ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Cusps.html#Subgroup.strictWidthInfty\">strictWidthInfty</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">⇑<span class=\"fn\">f</span></span>)</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.IsBigO\">=O[</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.IsBigO\">]</a>   <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">k</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Hecke's bound** for the coefficients of a cusp form: if `f` is a weight `k` modular form for\nan arithmetic subgroup, then its `q`-expansion coefficients are `O (n ^ (k / 2))`.\n\nThis is not optimal -- the optimal exponent is `(k - 1) / 2 + ε` for any `0 < ε`, at least for\ncongruence levels -- but is much easier to prove than the optimal result. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Bounds.html#CuspFormClass.qExpansion_isBigO","kind":"theorem","line":309,"name":"CuspFormClass.qExpansion_isBigO","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Bounds.lean#L309-L321"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Bounds.html#ModularFormClass.qExpansion_isBigO\"><span class=\"name\">ModularFormClass</span>.<span class=\"name\">qExpansion_isBigO</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hk</span> : <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Γ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Defs.html#Subgroup\">Subgroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/GeneralLinearGroup/Defs.html#Matrix.GeneralLinearGroup\">GL</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Γ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/ArithmeticSubgroups.html#Subgroup.IsArithmetic\">IsArithmetic</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/FunLike/Basic.html#FunLike\">FunLike</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/UpperHalfPlane/Basic.html#UpperHalfPlane\">UpperHalfPlane</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Basic.html#ModularFormClass\">ModularFormClass</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">Γ</span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">F</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.coeff\">PowerSeries.coeff</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/QExpansion.html#ModularFormClass.qExpansion\">qExpansion</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Γ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Cusps.html#Subgroup.strictWidthInfty\">strictWidthInfty</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">⇑<span class=\"fn\">f</span></span>)</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.IsBigO\">=O[</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/Defs.html#Asymptotics.IsBigO\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Bound for the coefficients of a modular form: if `f` is a weight `k` modular form for an\narithmetic subgroup, then its `q`-expansion coefficients are `O (n ^ k)`.\n\nThis is not optimal -- the optimal exponent is `k - 1 + ε` for any `0 < ε`, at least for congruence\nlevels -- but is much easier to prove than the optimal result.\n\nSee `CuspFormClass.qExpansion_isBigO` for a sharper bound assuming `f` is cuspidal. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Bounds.html#ModularFormClass.qExpansion_isBigO","kind":"theorem","line":289,"name":"ModularFormClass.qExpansion_isBigO","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Bounds.lean#L289-L307"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/Bounds.html#qExpansion_coeff_isBigO_of_norm_isBigO\"><span class=\"name\">qExpansion_coeff_isBigO_of_norm_isBigO</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">ℤ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Γ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Defs.html#Subgroup\">Subgroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/GeneralLinearGroup/Defs.html#Matrix.GeneralLinearGroup\">GL</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Γ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ModularForms/ArithmeticSubgroups.html#Subgroup.IsArithmetic\">IsArithmetic</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\